        <h2>Harm of ultraviolet light</h2>
        <p>Each year, there are more new cases of skin cancer diagnosed in the United States than new cases of breast, prostate, lung and colon cancers combined. One in five Americans will develop skin cancer in their lifetime. One American dies from skin cancer every hour. 
        Unprotected exposure to UV radiation is the most preventable risk factor for skin cancer.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.epa.gov/sunsafety/health-effects-uv-radiation">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
